## Additional Disclaimers

### System Modification Warning
This guide contains commands and procedures that modify system configurations. 
Users execute these commands at their own risk. The authors and contributors 
are not responsible for:

- Data loss or corruption
- System instability or failure
- Hardware damage
- Any other issues arising from following this guide

### Best Practices
Always:
- Create system backups (Timeshift snapshots) before major changes
- Test commands in a virtual machine when possible
- Understand what each command does before executing it
- Verify commands from trusted sources only
- Keep your system backed up regularly

### Hardware Compatibility
This guide has been tested on specific hardware configurations (Acer Swift 3 SF314, 
ASUS TUF F15). Results may vary with different hardware. Hardware-specific sections 
may require adjustments for your particular setup.

### Third-Party Software
This guide references and provides installation instructions for third-party software. 
Users should review the licenses and terms of service for all software they install. 
The authors of this guide are not affiliated with or responsible for third-party 
software mentioned herein.

### Official Documentation
Always refer to official documentation when available:
- [Ubuntu Documentation](https://help.ubuntu.com/)
- [NVIDIA Documentation](https://docs.nvidia.com/)
- Individual software project documentation

### Security Considerations
Commands requiring `sudo` grant administrative privileges. Always:
- Verify the source of commands before executing
- Understand what privileges are being granted
- Use trusted repositories and official sources
- Keep your system updated with security patches

By using this guide, you acknowledge these disclaimers and agree to use the 
information at your own risk and discretion.
